# Core boundaries

This mirror reflects **GridDungeon.Core** from the game repo. Authority: [core assembly improvement plan](https://github.com/miramocha/griddungeon-design-docs/blob/main/docs/plans/core-assembly-improvement-plan.md), [05-class-design](https://github.com/miramocha/griddungeon-design-docs/blob/main/docs/05-class-design.md).

## Dependency (game repo)

```
GridDungeon.Campaign  ‚Üí  GridDungeon.Core
GridDungeon.Runtime     ‚Üí  Core + Campaign
GridDungeon.Core        ‚Üí  (none)
```

This mirror ships **Core only** ‚Äî no Campaign or Runtime assemblies.

## Core owns

| Area | Examples in `src/` |
|---|---|
| Simulators / formulas | `DamageCalculator`, `MapRevealCalculator`, `TurnQueueBuilder` |
| Neutral models & DTOs | `ExplorationTarget`, `FloorExitLink`, combat models |
| Story **data shapes** | `StoryEventDefinitionData`, effect/step DTOs |
| Save schema | `SaveGame`, `CampaignSaveData`, mappers |
| Maze generation | `WilsonsMazeGenerator`, transmuters, `MazeGrid` |
| Generic hub rules | `GuildPartyRules` (slot count ‚Äî no campaign flag writes) |

## Not in Core (game repo elsewhere)

| Smell | Put in game repo |
|---|---|
| Story executors, trigger catalogs, `switch (storyEventId)` | `GridDungeon.Campaign` |
| S1 resolvers, floor keys, tutorial policy | `Campaign/` |
| `MonoBehaviour`, ScriptableObject, UITK | `Runtime/` / `UI/` |
| JsonUtility file I/O | Runtime `SaveSystem` |

## PR / agent checklist (when editing game Core)

1. Stratum- or story-specific? ‚Üí `Campaign/`, not Core.
2. Only a data shape? ‚Üí DTO in Core; behavior in Campaign or Runtime.
3. Would a second stratum duplicate constants? ‚Üí Campaign policy.
4. New `using` to Campaign/Runtime from Core? ‚Üí Stop ‚Äî refactor.

After game Core merge ‚Üí sync this mirror.
